const title = "Interacting Galaxies in HCG 77 - ArXiv Atlas";

import WikiLink from '../../components/WikiLink.astro';
---
<Base title={title}>
  <Sidebar />
  <main class="page-main">
    <h1 class="page-title">Interacting Galaxies in HCG 77</h1>
        
        <div class="infobox">
            <h3 class="infobox-title">AstroSat UVIT Observations of HCG 77</h3>
            <table>
                <tr>
                    <th>Paper:</th>
                    <td><a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2603.12173">arXiv:2603.12173</a></td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <th>Authors:</th>
                    <td>Srivastava et al.</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <th>Year:</th>
                    <td>2026</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <th>Journal:</th>
                    <td>Astronomy & Astrophysics</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <th>Type:</th>
                    <td>Observational study</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <th>Key Targets:</th>
                    <td>PGC 56121<br>PGC 56125<br>Tidal dwarf candidate</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <th>Related:</th>
                    <td><WikiLink slug="pages/Galaxy_Interactions" text="Galaxy Interactions" /><br>
                        <WikiLink slug="pages/Tidal_Features" text="Tidal Features" /><br>
                        <WikiLink slug="pages/Tidal_Dwarf_Galaxies" text="Tidal Dwarf Galaxies" /><br>
                        <WikiLink slug="pages/Star_Formation" text="Star Formation" /></td>
                </tr>
            </table>
        </div>

        <h2 id="section-0">Overview</h2>

        <p>This study uses the <WikiLink slug="pages/AstroSat" text="AstroSat" /> <WikiLink slug="pages/UVIT" text="Ultra Violet Imaging Telescope (UVIT)" /> in the far-ultraviolet (FUV) band to observe the possibly interacting galaxy pair PGC 56121 and PGC 56125 in <WikiLink slug="pages/Hickson_Compact_Groups" text="Hickson Compact Group 77 (HCG 77)" />. The high-resolution FUV observations reveal new details about <WikiLink slug="pages/Star_Formation" text="star formation" /> in the system and identify a candidate <WikiLink slug="pages/Tidal_Dwarf_Galaxies" text="tidal dwarf galaxy" />.</p>

        <h2 id="section-1">Main Findings</h2>

        <h3>High-Resolution FUV Imaging</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>AstroSat/UVIT provides significantly higher resolution than GALEX near-UV observations</li>
            <li>FUV images trace young, hot stellar populations more effectively than previous surveys (PS-1, DSS)</li>
            <li>Resolution improvements enable detailed study of <WikiLink slug="pages/Star_Forming_Regions" text="star-forming regions" /></li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Star-Forming Regions</h3>
        <p>Multiple star-forming regions identified in both PGC 56121 and PGC 56125, indicating active ongoing star formation triggered or enhanced by the <WikiLink slug="pages/Galaxy_Interactions" text="interaction" />.</p>

        <h3>Tidal Dwarf Galaxy Discovery</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Candidate tidal dwarf galaxy identified at the end of a tidal tail to the east of the pair</li>
            <li>Three major star-forming regions detected within the candidate tidal dwarf</li>
            <li>Provides observational evidence for <WikiLink slug="pages/Tidal_Dwarf_Galaxies" text="tidal dwarf galaxy formation" /> during galaxy interactions</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Kinematic-Redshift Separation</h3>
        <p>The two galaxies PGC 56121 and PGC 56125 are separated by large differences in redshift but appear in projection as an interacting pair. This suggests they may be a chance projection effect rather than a true physical interaction, though they are part of a small group of galaxies.</p>

        <h2 id="section-2">Spectral Energy Distribution Analysis</h2>

        <p>Broadband photometric analysis of all three galaxies yields key physical properties:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Stellar mass</strong> - Derived from multiwavelength SED fitting</li>
            <li><strong>Dust mass</strong> - Infrared-derived estimates of dust content</li>
            <li><strong>Total luminosity</strong> - Measured across wavelength range</li>
            <li><strong>Star formation history</strong> - Age structure and past and present SF rates</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 id="section-3">Supporting Observations</h2>

        <p>Comparison with <WikiLink slug="pages/Radio_Observations" text="radio observations" /> indicates the three galaxies are likely part of a small interacting group of galaxies. The radio data provide complementary information about ongoing star formation and AGN activity.</p>

        <h2 id="section-4">Open Questions</h2>

        <ul>
            <li>Is the apparent interaction between PGC 56121 and PGC 56125 a true dynamical interaction or a projection effect?</li>
            <li>What is the nature and survival prospects of the candidate tidal dwarf galaxy?</li>
            <li>How does UV-bright star formation relate to the system's dynamics?</li>
            <li>What is the detailed star formation history of each component?</li>
        </ul>

